obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `THE ACQUIRED TERRITORIES (MERGER) ACT, 1960`
  line `A CT No. 64 OF 1960`
  line `[28 th December, 1960.]`
  line `An Act to provide for the merger into the States of Assam, Punjab and West Bengal of certain`
  line `territories acquired in pursuance of the agreements entered into between the Governments`
  line `of India and Pakistan and for matters connected therewith.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Eleventh Year of the Republic of India as follows: ―`
  line `1. Short title.― This Act may be called the Acquired Territories (Merger) Act, 1960.`
  line `2. Definitions.― In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, ―`
  line `( a ) “ acquired territories ” mean so much of the territories comprised in the Indo-Pakistan`
  line `agreements and referred to in the First Schedule as are demarcated for the purpose of being`
  line `acquired by India in pursuance of the said agreements;`
  line `( b ) “ appointed day ” means such date 1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint for the merger of the acquired territories under section 3, after causing`
  line `the territories to be so acquired demarcated for the purpose, and different dates may be appointed`
  line `for the merger of such territories into different States;`
  line `( c ) “ assembly constituency ”, “ council constituency ” and “ parliamentary constituency ” have`
  line `the same meanings as in the Representation of the People Act, 1950 (43 of 1950);`
  line `( d ) “ Indo-Pakistan agreements ” mean the Agreements dated the 10th day of September, 1958,`
  line `the 23rd day of October, 1959 and the 11th day of January, 1960 entered into between the`
  line `Governments of India and Pakistan, the relevant extracts of which are set out in the Second`
  line Schedule;
  line `( e ) “ law ” includes any enactment, ordinance, regulation, order, bye-law, rule, scheme,`
  line `notification or other instrument having the force of law in the whole or in any part of the acquired`
  line territory;
  line `( f ) “ sitting member ”, in relation to either House of Parliament or of the Legislature of a State,`
  line `means a person who, immediately before the appointed day, is a member of that House;`
  line `( g ) “ State concerned ”, in relation to the acquired territories referred to in Part I, Part II and`
  line `Part III of the First Schedule, means, respectively, the State of Assam, the State of Punjab and the`
  line `State of West Bengal; and “ State Government concerned ” shall be construed accordingly;`
  line `( h ) “ Union purposes ” mean the purposes of Government relatable to any of the matters`
  line `mentioned in List I of the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution.`
  line `3. Merger of acquired territories.― ( 1 ) As from the appointed day, the acquired territories`
  line `referred to in Part I, Part II and Part III of the First Schedule shall, respectively be included in, and`
  line `form part of the States of Assam, Punjab and West Bengal.`
  line `( 2 ) As from the appointed day, the State Government concerned shall, by order in the Official`
  line `Gazette, provide for the administration of the acquired territories included in that State by including`
  line `them or any part of them in such district, sub-division, police station or other administrative unit as`
  line `may be specified in the order.`
  line `1. 17th January, 1961, vide notification No. G.S.R. 74, dated 14th January, 1961, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3( i ).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-3
  sectionNo (3)
