  title `Page 3`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  sourcePage 3
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `4. Amendment of the First Schedule to the Constitution.― As from the appointed day, in the`
  line `First Schedule to the Constitution, ―`
  line `( a ) in the paragraph relating to the territories of the State of Assam, after the words “ the`
  line `Assam Tribal Areas ”, the words, figures and brackets “ and the territories referred to in Part I of`
  line `the First Schedule to the Acquired Territories (Merger) Act, 1960 ” shall be inserted;`
  line `( b ) in the paragraph relating to the territories of the State of Punjab, after the words and`
  line `figures “ the States Reorganisation Act, 1956 (37 of 1956) ”, the words, figures and brackets “ and`
  line `the territories referred to in Part II of the First Schedule to the Acquired Territories (Merger) Act,`
  line `1960 ” shall be inserted;`
  line `( c ) in the paragraph relating to the territories of the State of West Bengal, after the words,`
  line `brackets and figures “ the Bihar and West Bengal (Transfer of Territories) Act, 1956 (40 of`
  line `1956) ”, the words, figures and brackets “ and the territories referred to in Part III of the First`
  line `Schedule to the Acquired Territories (Merger) Act, 1960 ” shall be inserted.`
  line `5. Construction of references to existing constituencies. ― As from the appointed day, ―`
  line `( a ) any reference in the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies`
  line `Order, 1956, ―`
  line `( i ) to the State of Assam or Punjab or West Bengal, shall be construed as including that`
  line `part of the acquired territory which is included in that State;`
  line `( ii ) to any district, sub-division, police station or other administrative unit, shall be`
  line `construed as including that part of the acquired territory, if any, which is included in that`
  line `district, sub-division, police station or other administrative unit, by order made under`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 3;`
  line `( b ) any reference in the Delimitation of Council Constituencies (Punjab) Order, 1951 ―`
  line `( i ) to the State of Punjab, shall be construed as including that part of the acquired territory`
  line `which is included in that State;`
  line `( ii ) to any district, shall be construed as including that part of the acquired territory, if`
  line `any, which is included in that district, by order made under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 3;`
  line `( c ) any reference in the Delimitation of Council Constituencies (West Bengal) Order, 1951 ―`
  line `( i ) to the State of West Bengal, shall be construed as including that part of the acquired`
  line `territory which is included in that State;`
  line `( ii ) to any division or district, shall be construed as including the acquired territory, if any,`
  line `which is included in that division or district, by order made under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 3.`
  line `6. Provisions as to sitting members.― ( 1 ) Every sitting member of the House of the People`
  line `representing any parliamentary constituency the extent of which has been altered by virtue of the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall, notwithstanding such alteration, be deemed to have been elected as from`
  line `the appointed day to that House by that constituency as so altered.`
  line `( 2 ) Every sitting member of the Legislative Assembly of the State of Assam or Punjab or West`
  line `Bengal representing any assembly constituency the extent of which has been altered by virtue of the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall, notwithstanding such alteration, be deemed to have been elected as from`
  line `the appointed day to the said Legislative Assembly by that constituency as so altered.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-4
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Page 4`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  sourcePage 4
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line 4
  line `( 3 ) Every sitting member of the Legislative Council of Punjab or West Bengal representing any`
  line `Council constituency the extent of which has been altered by virtue of the provisions of this Act, shall,`
  line `notwithstanding such alteration, be deemed to have been elected as from the appointed day to the said`
  line `Legislative Council by that constituency as so altered.`
  line `7. Property and assets. ― ( 1 ) All property and assets within the acquired territories which`
  line `immediately before the appointed day, are vested in Pakistan or in the Province of East Pakistan or the`
  line `Province of West Pakistan shall, as from that day, ―`
  line `( a ) where such property and assets are relatable to Union purposes, vest in the Union;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, vest in the State concerned in which the acquired territories are`
  line included.
  line `( 2 ) A certificate of the Central Government signed by a Secretary to that Government shall be`
  line `conclusive as to whether the purposes for which any property or assets are held, immediately before`
  line `the appointed day, are Union purposes.`
  line `8. Appropriation of moneys for expenditure in acquired territories. ― ( 1 ) As from the`
  line `appointed day, any Act passed by the Legislature of the State of Assam or Punjab or West Bengal`
  line `before that day for the appropriation of any moneys out of the Consolidated Fund of that State to meet`
  line `any expenditure in respect of any part of the financial year 1960-61, shall have effect also in relation`
  line `to the acquired territories included in that State and it shall be lawful for the State Government`
  line `concerned to spend any amount in respect of those territories out of the amount authorised by such`
  line `Act to be expenditure for any service in that State.`
  line `( 2 ) The Governor of the State concerned may, after the appointed day, authorise such expenditure`
  line `from the Consolidated Fund of that State as he deems necessary for any purpose or service in the`
  line `acquired territories included in that State for a period of not more than three months beginning with`
  line `the appointed day pending the sanction of such expenditure by the Legislature of that State.`
  line `9. Extension of laws.― All laws in force in the acquired territories immediately before the`
  line `appointed day shall, as from that day, cease to be in force in those territories and all laws in force`
  line `generally in the State concerned in which the acquired territories are included shall, as from that day,`
  line `extend to, or as the case may be, come into force in, those territories:`
  line `Provided that anything done or any action taken before the appointed day under any law in force`
  line `in the acquired territories shall be deemed to have been done or taken, as from the appointed day,`
  line `under the corresponding law extended to, and in force, in those territories.`
  line `10. Power to name authorities for exercising statutory functions.― The State Government`
  line `concerned, as respects the acquired territories included in that State, may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify the authority, officer or person who, on or after the appointed day, shall be`
  line `competent to exercise such functions, exercisable under any law in force on that day in those`
  line `territories, as may be mentioned in that notification and such law shall have effect accordingly.`
  line `11. Power to remove difficulties. ― ( 1 ) If any difficulty arises in relation to the transition from`
  line `any corresponding law to any law which by virtue of section 9 shall, as from the appointed day,`
  line `extend to, or come into force in, the acquired territories, the Central Government may, by order`
  line `notified in the Official Gazette, make such provisions as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removing the difficulty.`
  line `( 2 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act (otherwise than in relation`
  line `to the transition from any corresponding law) or in connection with the administration of the acquired`
  line `territories as a part of the State in which they are included, the State Government concerned may, by`
  line `order in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the purposes of this Act, as`
  line `appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-5
