  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  sourcePage 6
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line 6
  line `THE FIRST SCHEDULE`
  line `[ See sections 2( a ), 2( g ), 3 and 4]`
  line `P ART I`
  line `The acquired territory in relation to item ( 7 ) of paragraph 2 of the Agreement dated the 10th day`
  line `of September, 1958.`
  line `P ART II`
  line `The acquired territory in relation to item ( ii ) and item ( iii ) of paragraph 1 of the Agreement dated`
  line `the 11th day of January, 1960.`
  line `P ART III`
  line `The acquired territory in relation to item ( 5 ) and item ( 10 ) of paragraph 2 of the Agreement dated`
  line `the 10th day of September, 1958 and paragraph 4 of the Agreement dated the 23rd day of October,`
  line 1959.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-7
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Page 7`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  sourcePage 7
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `THE SECOND SCHEDULE`
  line `[ See section 2( d )]`
  line `1. E XTRACTS FROM THE N OTE CONTAINING THE A GREEMENT DATED THE 10 TH DAY OF`
  line `S EPTEMBER, 1958.`
  line `* * * * *`
  line `2. As a result of the discussions, the following agreements were arrived at: ―`
  line `* * * * *`
  line `(5) 24 Parganas ― Khulna`
  line `24 Parganas ― Jessore ―Boundary disputes.`
  line `It is agreed that the mean of the two respective claims of India and Pakistan should be adopted,`
  line `taking the river as a guide, as far as possible, in the case of the latter dispute. (Ichhamati river).`
  line `* * * * *`
  line `( 7 ) Piyain and Surma river regions to be demarcated in accordance with the relevant notifications,`
  line `cadastral survey maps and, if necessary, record of rights. Whatever the result of this demarcation`
  line `might be, the nationals of both the Governments to have the facility of navigation on both these rivers.`
  line `* * * * *`
  line `( 10 ) Exchange of old Cooch Behar enclaves in Pakistan and Pakistan enclaves in India without`
  line `claim to compensation for extra area going to Pakistan, is agreed to.`
  line `* * * * *`
  line `Signed. ( M.S.A. BAIG) Signed. (M. J. DESAI)`
  line `Foreign Secretary, Commonwealth Secretary,`
  line `Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Commonwealth Relations, Ministry of External Affairs,`
  line `Government of Pakistan. Government of India.`
  line `N EW D ELHI, S EPTEMBER, 10, 1958.`
  line `2. E XTRACTS FROM THE A GREEMENT ENTITLED “ A GREED D ECISIONS AND P ROCEDURES TO END`
  line `DISPUTES AND INCIDENTS ALONG THE I NDO- E AST P AKISTAN BORDER AREAS ”, DATED THE 23 RD DAY`
  line `OF O CTOBER, 1959.`
  line `* * * * *`
  line `4. West Bengal ― East Pakistan Boundary.`
  line `Over 1,200 miles of this boundary have already been demarcated. As regards the boundary`
  line `between West Bengal and East Pakistan in the areas of Mahanada, Burung and Karatoa rivers, it was`
  line `agreed that demarcation will be made in accordance with the latest cadastral survey maps supported`
  line `by relevant notifications and record of rights.`
  line `* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-8
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Page 8`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  sourcePage 8
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line 8
  line `(Sd.) (J. G. KHARAS) (Sd.) (M. J. DESAI)`
  line `Acting Foreign Secretary, Commonwealth Secretary,`
  line `Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Commonwealth Relations Ministry of External Affairs,`
  line `Karachi, New Delhi.`
  line `N EW D ELHI,`
  line `October 23, 1959.`
  line `3. E XTRACTS FROM THE A GREEMENT ENTITLED “ AGREED DECISIONS AND PROCEDURES TO END`
  line `DISPUTES AND INCIDENTS ALONG THE I NDO- W EST P AKISTAN BORDER AREAS ”, DATED THE 11TH DAY`
  line `OF J ANUARY, 1960.`
  line `* * * * *`
  line `1. West Pakistan-Punjab border. ― Of the total of 325 miles of the border in this sector,`
  line `demarcation has been completed along about 252 miles. About 73 miles of the border has not yet been`
  line `demarcated due to differences between the Governments of India and Pakistan regarding`
  line `interpretation of the decision and Award of the Punjab Boundary Commission presented by Sir Cyril`
  line `Radcliffe as Chairman of the Commission. These differences have been settled along the lines given`
  line `below in a spirit of accommodation:`
  line `* * * * *`
  line `( ii ) Chak Ladheke ( Amritsar-Lahore border ). ― The Governments of India and Pakistan agree`
  line `that the delineation of the boundary will be as shown in the map of the Kasur Tehsil by Sir Cyril`
  line `Radcliffe and Chak Ladheke will in consequence fall within the territorial jurisdiction of the`
  line `Government of India.`
  line `( iii ) Ferozepur ( Lahore-Ferozepur border ). ― The Governments of India and Pakistan agree`
  line `that the West Pakistan-Punjab (India) boundary in this region is along the district boundaries of`
  line `these districts and not along the actual course of the river Sutlej.`
  line `* * * * *`
  line `(Sd.) M. J. DESAI, (Sd.) J. G. KHARAS,`
  line `Commonwealth Secretary, Joint Secretary,`
  line `Ministry of External Affairs, Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Commonwealth Relations,`
  line `Government of India. Government of Pakistan.`
  line `N EW D ELHI;`
  line `January 11, 1960.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
